title: Grateful Dead Live at Oregon Country Fair on 1982-08-28
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) -> Sound Devices 744T (24bit/44.1k) -> Adobe Audition v3.0 -> Samplitude Professional v11.2 -> FLAC/16
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Minglewood Blues, Tennessee Jed, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Althea, It's All Over Now, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Day Job-> Women Are Smarter, West L.A. Fadeaway, Far From Me-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> The Wheel-> The Other One-> Truckin'-> Black Peter-> Playin' In The Band-> One More Saturday Night, E: Dupree's Diamond Blues

Springfield Creamery Presents the Second Decadenal Field TripOther artist(s): Peter Rowan; The Flying Karamozov Brothers; Strangers with Candy; Robert Cray Band;Tattoo

Held at the site of the Oregon Country Fair Grounds.  It is NOT the Oregon State Fair Grounds NOR the Oregon County Fair Grounds.

reviews.review_text: Crushing Devastating audience recording of a blistering performance. Wheel > Other One > Truckin?? How smokin is that???

Great recording So I went to this show. And soon after got a great soundboard that I had until about 5 years ago when I got rid of my tapes (my bad). 

But I did so because of this site.....lol

And since then have alwyas listened to the soundboards on here which were even better then my tape as it had a slight issue with fast pitch.

That being said I listened to this audience today and was transported back 20 years. It was like I was there again and thats on my speaker system (good) hooked up to my computer in my home office.

Amazing. This great stuff. Thank you!

BTW - my own personal score card has this as the all time Best Althea
- Pretty darn good! Obviously not a patch on the "Sunshine Daydream" show the decade before...but at least they MADE this one, unlike '93...

Best Love the 1st person to review this one. I think the way who ever it is wrote the comment is one of BEST descriptions I have ever read.
 Reviewer: Franklin's Towel - 5.00 out of 5 stars5.00 out of 5 stars5.00 out of 5 stars5.00 out of 5 stars5.00 out of 5 stars - July 15, 2011 

Subject: Crushing 
 
Devastating audience recording of a blistering performance.
 Wheel > Other One > Truckin?? How smokin is that???

Agreed In total agreement with FT's take. I was at that show and it sounds EXACTLY as I remembered it. This audience recording easily trumps the soundboard for authenticity imo. And kudos to Mr. Wagner and Mr. Miller for their efforts. This is a no brainer. 

Five stars all around.
